==English==
===Pronunciation===
/{{IPAchar|ɪˈɹeɪz}}/, /<tt>I"r\eIz</tt>/
*:Rhymes: [[Rhymes:English:-eɪs|-eɪs]], [[Rhymes:English:-eɪz|-eɪz]]
===Transitive verb===
'''erase'''
#to [[remove]] [[mark]]ings or [[information]]
#: ''I '''erased''' that note because it was wrong.''
#''([[storage]])'' To [[obliterate]] [[information]] from a [[storage]] [[medium]], such as to [[clear]] or to [[overwrite]]  
#: ''I'm going to '''erase''' those files.''
#''(magnetic storage)'' to remove all stored [[data]] by (a) changing the medium to an unmagnetized state or (b) changing the medium to a predetermined magnetized state. 
#: ''I'm going to '''erase''' that tape.''
#''(paper tape storage)'' ''(punched card storage)'' to punch a hole at every punch position.
#{{baseball}} To remove a [[runner]] from the bases via a [[double play]] or pick off play
#: ''Jones was '''erased''' by a 6-4-3 double play.''

Source: definitions from [[Federal Standard 1037C]] and from [[MIL-STD-188]]
